ic":0.8,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level PR summary comment has a matching inline comment posted at the relevant line","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure is data inconsistency between two separately generated outputs: inline comments and the summary comment. Testing the inline comment generator alone (Unit) won't catch if the summary builder drops a finding. Testing the summary builder alone won't catch if inline comments failed to post. The failure appears at the module boundary—when data flows from comment generation through to summary aggregation. Integration testing both modules together with mocked GitHub API captures this data-flow failure.","test_description":"Mock the GitHub API for posting comments. Generate the full set of inline comments for a review, then generate the summary comment. Extract all findings from the summary comment text. Verify that each finding in the summary corresponds to exactly one inline comment. Check for both false positives (summary lists findings not commented) and false negatives (comments posted but not in summary).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Integration testing of multiple modules wired together catches the boundary failure. A Unit test of either module alone would pass even if the other module fails to send data (Unit confidence 0.25 is secondary).","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The complete end-to-end sequence—reading a real PR diff, analyzing code with AI, posting inline comments, and creating a summary comment—completes without hanging, errors, or manual intervention","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This tests orchestration of multiple steps in sequence: read PR from GitHub → analyze with LLM → post inline comments to GitHub → post summary. At least one step is Agentic (LLM analysis). The failure modes are deadlocks, race conditions, or state inconsistencies that only surface when all steps run together in order. Testing fewer steps (Unit, Integration, Agentic in isolation) won't catch orchestration-level failures like 'comments post before summary is ready' or 'LLM analysis times out blocking comment posting'.","test_description":"Create a real GitHub pull request with known code defects. Execute the full agent pipeline against the real PR, from reading the PR diff through posting the final summary comment. Verify: (1) no errors or hangs occur, (2) the process completes within a timeout, (3) all inline comments are posted, (4) the summary comment appears, (5) at least one defect is identified (per behavior 3), and (6) findings match comments (per behavior 4).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Workflow level is needed because the failure is in orchestration across multiple steps, including an Agentic step. An Integration-level test with mocked GitHub and LLM might pass but fail on real systems (System concerns at 0.25). Workflow encompasses the orchestration.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.25,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.55}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12863,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12863},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6174a379-58f4-42d1-95e2-eb0cb06def18","uuid":"870ef86c-0926-4639-a19b-00210eca9ef2"}
